[3] France final follow-up report to the OIE
Date: Wed 21 May 2008
Source: OIE, WAHID interface [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=7056>


Bluetongue, France - Follow-up report No. 34 (Final report)
-----------------------------------------------------------
Information received on 21 May 2008 from Dr. Monique Eloit,
Directrice generale adjointe, Direction generale de l'alimentation,
Ministere de l'Agriculture et de la Peche, PARIS Cedex 15, France

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 34 (Final report)
Start date: 19 Jul 2007
Date of first confirmation of the event: 19 Jul 2007
Report date: 21 May 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 21 May 2008
Date event resolved: 21 May 2008
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2006
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports:

-Immediate notification (28 Jul 2007)

New outbreaks
[This follow-up report No 34, includes the locations of 5 new
outbreaks which had started during May 2008 in the provinces
MAINE-ET-LOIRE, VENDEE, CORREZE, CREUSE and HAUTE-VIENNE. A map is
included. The total number of affected animals was 6 (cattle). An
administrative map of France can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/europe/france_admin91.jpg>. - Mod.AS]

Future Reporting
The event is unlikely to be contained and is now considered to be
endemic. No more follow-up reports will be made, but instead,
information about this disease will be included in the future
6-monthly reports.

